.IX Title "StrfClock 3"
.TH StrfClock 3 "perl v5.6.1" "2000-05-24" "User Contributed Perl Documentation"
.UC
.SH "NAME"
Tk::StrfClock \- a X/TK digital clock widget based on strftime.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&  use Tk::StrfClock;
.Ve
.Vb 5
\&  $top->StrfClock(
\&        -format => <strftime format string>,
\&        -update => [<seconds>|s|m|h|d],
\&        -advance => [<seconds>],
\&  );
.Ve
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Tk::StrfClock is a digital clock widget, with all the other attributes
of a Tk::Label.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.IX Header "OPTIONS"
.Sh "\-format => <strftime format string>"
.IX Subsection "-format => <strftime format string>"
.Vb 2
\&        Sets the required date/time format using POSIX strftime format.
\&        The default is "%I:%M:%S%p, %A, %e %B %Y.".
.Ve
.Sh "\-update => <seconds>|s|m|h|d|a"
.IX Subsection "-update => <seconds>|s|m|h|d|a"
.Vb 3
\&        Sets how often the clock is updated.  If set to the characters
\&        s, m, h, d or a then the clock is updated exactly on the second,
\&        minute, hour, day or is automatically guessed.
.Ve
.Vb 1
\&        The default is 'a'.
.Ve
.Sh "\-advance => <seconds>"
.IX Subsection "-advance => <seconds>"
.Vb 2
\&        Sets the clock fast or slow this many seconds. The default is
\&        0.
.Ve
.Sh "Other Tk::Label options."
.IX Subsection "Other Tk::Label options."
.SH "MINIMAL EXAMPLE"
.IX Header "MINIMAL EXAMPLE"
.Vb 2
\&  use Tk;
\&  use Tk::StrfClock;
.Ve
.Vb 3
\&  my $top=MainWindow->new();
\&  $top->StrfClock()->pack();
\&  MainLoop();
.Ve
